<p>
    Visual Studio and Visual Studio Code automatically support TypeScript and come with it (the compiler) installed.
    However, if you need to or want to install it manually, read below.
</p>

<p>The compiler (included with TypeScript) is known as <code>tsc</code>.</p>

<p>
    To see what version is installed, type <code>tsc -v</code> or <code>tsc --version</code> at a Powershell command prompt.
</p>

